annotation.TEXT: ...Did I just clip through the head of that cannon?! (Nuts, I forgot to do a slow-motion instant replay of that when I put together this video. Click here to go back to 8:32 to watch it again.)
I've gotta be careful with swimming in the water, because I might get body slammed or poked by Spikitu.
BGM: Kirby Super Star Ultra - Masked Dedede Theme
Hmm... This water slows down the descent rate of the spinies (thanks to sprite buoyancy being on), and I think that actually makes avoiding them slightly easier.
Whoa! I somehow avoided getting kersplodered there!
Okay, I'm past that... Whoa, watch out for that upwards-moving bat.
Aah, what's with the music here? It sounds so... Aahhh!!! This isn't right! Hey, Spikitu! Do you know why the music is all screwed up?
I think I'll check out this upper path first.
This doesn't seem too difficult...
Wait, this seems familiar...
Whoa! I got lucky there!
There's another T piece, useful for T-spin singles, doubles, and triples, which usually score points at a better rate than regular Tetrises in the games that acknowledge them.
And somehow, I managed to get a 40, despite the music trying to mess with my mind... games... mind... games...
BGM: CUSTOM - Castle Melody...? Oh, god! What the heck?!
Spikitu himself is still fireproof, and I imagine he's wearing earplugs as well...
Okay, let's get these flames to despawn before I go any further.
Alright, all there was on the lower path here were those four coin blocks, a bat, and a fireball-shooting statue.

I wonder if I can do that glitch where my most recent fireball goes "poof" while overlapping the boss, and damages the boss continuously... Nah, I think the boss is too far away from the wall for that to work.
Zwee! Somehow, I still have all of my limbs and other essential body parts, so that's good.
Yiiiihhhh!!!! Umm... Luigi? How are you not a pancake now after that foolish move I just made?!
Oh, man. There's a boss battle.
As expected, that unlocked a warp star, but it also revealed a path leading down here...
Anything special down here involving these blocks that those bats started on? ...No? This might've been a good place to hide a secret...
There's a flower that I don't currently need.
Ha! That bat got kersplodered!
Aw, man. Do I really have to play the waiting game here? I'd rather play Hungry Hungry Hippos instead.
Good thing the Substitute Jizo lasted just long enough for me to endure all that! (And let me get tons of graze!)
BGM: CUSTOM - Star Shock by ThinkOneMoreTime
The water doesn't seem to affect the Thwimp's movement at all, but I don't think water has ever affected Thwimps, has it?
Good luck with trying to clear that one without using items, though!

Luigi has no clue. Well, whatever. Now, I can wall jump off of layer 2 wall, but oddly, I can't seem to wall jump at all while I'm being pushed against the edge of the screen for some reason, which led to that near-pancake situation there.
That was a rather obvious hidden block.
Those jumps with the Thwomp up ahead look tricky. I'm trying to see if I can use screen scrolling to trick the Thwomp into stomping early.
That was a miss and a close call.
And suddenly, screen transition.
Yeek! Barely avoided another explosion there! (..."Yeek"? What kind of weird word is that?)

Hello, and welcome back to Something else! So, will the next level be Bullet Bird Boom on my right, or Spikitu Castle 2 * on my left? ...Or maybe it'll be The Last Castle on the far right, but I hightly doubt it...
At least this level isn't autoscrolling like the first Spikitu Castle * was.
Yeah, I thought I saw that block down there, but there doesn't seem to be anything of interest to me regarding it.
Oh, geez... The dropping pitch of that one note in the music there...
Yeah, I'm going to anticipate that all ledges that look like that and are at least four tiles long will drop.

Okay, seriously. Why am I having trouble climbing up these ice blocks? And why hasn't YouTube fixed that annoying annotation editor glitch involving annotations' default starting times that occurs when I'm in the last 5% of the video yet?
These ice blocks are slippery, but not the entire level. I don't slip around when I walk on other things. Also, these ice blocks can't be fried.
And, there's the goal! Awesome!
And there's our exploding pink bullet birds. Fortunately, I can stomp them normally and that'll keep them from blowing up.
This music, man... It sounds like someone's blowing their nose in a trumpet or something. I don't know.
Huh. It looks like the cannon on the right here is firing red birds. So, I take it that those are just normal birds that don't explode? Also, this part looks tricky...

Okay, so we've got a baseball guy on the right that I can't do anything about, and a cannon on the left that's moving up and down while shooting Pidgit Bills. I guess I need to bounce off the birds in order to target that Lakitu up there.
No, that screwy music is still here! Argh!!! Also, we've got autoscrolling now, so I can't even try to race through this area.
Oh, man. So many ice blocks...
There's a couple of T pieces. Now we just need the square, line, S, Z, and L pieces...
Also, it might be a good idea to add a way for a non-peachy plumber to escape here, just in case.
Whoa, what? If that cannon housed the pink birds, they'd've exploded immediately upon being fired!

Alright, that Lakitu is flammable/inflammable at least. He's probably like nearly every boss from Touhou Mario: Imperishable Night, actually. (Isn't that custom boss called the "Noob Boss" or something like that?)
We've got Centaur Man water as well...
Yeah, I can still get burninating power from it. Agh, that music, though...
Oh, god! AAAHHH!!!
I considered turning off the layer that the snow is on to improve the frame rate, but the snow is on layer 1, so doing that would make all of the other objects around here invisible, unfortunately.
Yeah, nuts to this!
And, I'm back to where I found that obvious hidden block, so let's go back to the right now.
And that leads there, which was expected.
Now, there is the distinct possibility that this is the last normal goal I'll go through in this hack, because...
Oh, I wonder if that bird would've blown up that golden statue back there if I had let it...
Wah! Okay, enough with the close calls already!

...clearing this level reveals another path leading to The Last Castle. Of course, there might be normal goals in the special world, but I don't know if that's the case yet. So, next time, I will be taking on The Last Castle! To be continued...
Bah, really? Well, so much for keeping all of my essential body parts, though I still have enough to get by, for now...
Yeah, I thought that piece of land was gonna fall there. Man, what's happened to this place? Did The Evil Guy do this to your castle, Spikitu?
Whoa! Okay, don't panic. The birds won't explode in the middle of the room, so there's little to worry about as long as I stay away from the sides.
BGM: Touhou 14.3: Impossible Spell Card - Eternal Transient Reign
So, is that statue there gonna breathe fire? ...No? Okay, then.
Yeah, I thought that would be a multi-coin block.
Wo, ym niarb! I emalb eht cisum rof taht eno.
Woo! Already, the peach saved my bacon from being cooked!
12 coins. That's not very good.
25 coins. That's pretty good.
Alright, let's take on Bullet Bird Boom now!
Yay, I'm done!
Goal tape average so far: 1710 / 50 = 34.2 stars each.
Oh, thank god! We're using a non-screwy music now!
Looks like this is a vertical level with moving layer 2 platforms.
Oh, good. Midpoint. Please tell me that the second half of the level changes the music!
Also, I think stomping the boss does more damage than shooting it with a fireball, so I should try for stomps more often.
Watch out. There's more boom-birds here.
Alright, since Spikitu Castle 2 * won by a whopping 9 1/3 votes, I'm heading there next!
Maybe I could get it to work if I managed to get a fireball to hit a Pidgit Bill while it was overlapping the boss, but that looks way too tricky, if not impossible, so I'll just forget about that.
Also, what's with that off-color flower? Does it still work correctly?
Ah, that links to Darkave. Alright.
So, Remilia's tossing knives everywhere...
Oh, god, that music. Just finish the level already!
Wait, are they getting faster?
That looks like a J piece from Tetris.
Goal tape average so far: 1670 / 49 = 34.082 stars each.
D'oh. I was expecting a power up and not a multi-coin block this time.
Ah, forget it! Just go!
Ooh, peachy. I think that'll be a lot more useful than fireballs would've been here.
Oh, man. The pink bullet birds explode? I'd better watch out for that.
Okay, how did I not get kersplodered there? I think it's because the explosion is not actually harmful during its first few frames.
Huh, I wonder why that Thwomp is on the floor like that if it's not a maverick or some other special variety? Also, there was a 1-up there that I barely saw before collecting it.
If the video seems to be a bit choppy now, I blame the blizzard here. That kind of thing is generally not good for the frame rate for some reason.
Oh, I guess I didn't have to wait around down there! Nice!
BGM: CUSTOM - Castle Melody...?
I have to always be mindful of the solid objects that are lined up with bullet cannons here, because of how the birds go boom when they hit something solid.
Oh, Spikitu's going away? Does that mean I'm done with this level? But, that was kind of a short second half...
